<p>Reports invalid prefixes defined in the <code>@ConfigurationProperties</code> annotations
  and incorrect property binding via constructor in Spring components.
</p>

<ul>
  The reported issues with prefixes include:
  <li>Missing prefix</li>
  <li>Empty prefix</li>
  <li>Prefix in notation other than the kebab-case</li>
</ul>

<p>
  The property binding error is reported if a Spring component annotated with <code>@ConfigurationProperties</code>
  has parameters other than injected beans in the constructor. Constructor cannot be used for property binding
  in Spring components because it is used for bean injection in this case. Binding via setters should be used instead.
</p>

<p>
  The inspection also reports classes that are annotated with <code>@ConfigurationProperties</code>
  and not registered via <code>@EnableConfigurationProperties</code>,
  marked as a Spring component, or scanned via <code>@ConfigurationPropertiesScan</code>.
</p>
<!-- tooltip end -->
<p>
  This inspection only triggers in classes annotated with <code>@ConfigurationProperties</code> that are not scanned via <code>@ConfigurationPropertiesScan</code>
  when the Spring Boot version for the project or module is set to 2.2.0 or later.
</p>
